<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[72145]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[In search of happiness]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[Las cosas que faltan comes to the Versus Teatre to reflect on a couple's yearnings to become parents.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>Martín and Jaume are a couple who wish to become parents, but the processes for adopting are very complicated and no money can change hands for a legal surrogacy in some countries.</p>
<p>Laura is the woman who offers a solution. Renting out her womb for a tidy sum of money, and under one condition: disappearing for ever from life. This is the starting point for Las cosas que faltan, a play that is playing throughout August at the Versus Teatre.</p>
